post_text:
How will the District use the bond proceeds?

A new Upper Elementary school for 4th and 5th grades. The facility will be built on property already owned by the North Pike School District and will also be designed to accommodate an additional grade when needed.

The existing Elementary School will get a new secure entry vestibule at the front entry and an existing classroom will be renovated to be the front office.

The Middle School will get a new vestibule at the main entry and air conditioning for the gymnasium.

The High School will have four added classrooms and toilet, renovation for the existing band hall, and a major addition for a new band hall for practice and storage.

Please vote YES to bring these much needed improvements to our great District!

Support us in providing the children of North Pike a better environment in which to learn and grow!

Vote YES on the Bond Issue!
